Although the Civil Service code should always be applied when carrying out research on behalf of the department, during a pre-election period, you should especially:

<li>keep contact with users limited to operational communications only (e.g. for recruitment purposes or to provide updates on research session details)
<li>continue to be mindful of how you use social media - 'likes' on social media can be seen as direct endorsements, and any posts or comments made are also open to public scrutiny.
